scit's clouds in the news video stanford department of classics skip to navigation department of classics standford university logo header home people programs courses projects news events resources contact scit's clouds in the news video submitted by ryan johnson on wed 05 12 2010 10 31am the student group stanford classics in theater founded and run by classics graduate and undergraduate students is staging a production of aristophanes play clouds this friday and saturday the production has been written up on the stanford report the university's main news service and on the human experience website produced by the stanford humanities center which just published stanford classics in theater to perform an ancient satire with modern obscenities check it out for a good synopsis of the hard work and serious play behind the production the stanford classics in theater website provides directions and other info admission is free so come join the fun and for a taste of of scit's talents view video clips below from last year's production of aristophanes the acharnians email stanford classics find us on facebook address & phone search upcoming events james rives animal sacrifice and social relations in judaea and rome 03 07 2012 see more site info 2012 stanford university department of classics all rights reserved site design by chapter three login login with sunet speaker request webform for faculty stanford classics wikisite powered by drupal an open source content management system
